{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MC28VLxJzQfXGPaC2S7Bzd","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Verification Proof: 17-2-lane-pool\n2\t\n3\tStory: Lane Pool\n4\tVerified: 2026-04-04T00:30:00Z\n5\tTier: test-provable\n6\t\n7\t## Summary\n8\t\n9\tVerdict: ALL_PASS\n10\tACs passed: 12/12\n11\t\n12\t## Build & Test Baseline\n13\t\n14\t- **Build:** PASS — `npm run build` completed successfully (tsup, ESM output)\n15\t- **Vitest:** PASS — 4840 passed across 179 test files, 0 failures\n16\t- **Lane-pool tests:** 27 passed (0 failed) in `src/lib/__tests__/lane-pool.test.ts`\n17\t- **Coverage:** `lane-pool.ts` — 100% Stmts, 91.17% Branch, 100% Funcs, 100% Lines\n18\t\n19\t## AC 1: Lane creation via WorktreeManager\n20\t**Verdict:** PASS\n21\t**Evidence:**\n22\t- `src/lib/lane-pool.ts` exists, exports `LanePool` class with `startPool(epics, executeFn)` method (line 174)\n23\t- `createLane()` private method calls `this.worktreeManager.createWorktree(epic.id, epic.slug)` (line 337)\n24\t- Test `creates worktrees via WorktreeManager for each lane` (line 120) asserts `mockWtm.createWorktree` called with correct args\n25\t\n26\t## AC 2: maxParallel concurrency enforcement\n27\t**Verdict:** PASS\n28\t**Evidence:**\n29\t- Test `limits concurrent executions to maxParallel` (line 134) uses maxParallel=2 with 4 epics\n30\t- Tracks `maxConcurrent` via atomic counter, asserts it never exceeds 2\n31\t- Uses deferred resolvers to control timing, verifies only 2 resolvers exist before any completion\n32\t\n33\t## AC 3: Each lane runs executeEpic callback with worktree path as cwd\n34\t**Verdict:** PASS\n35\t**Evidence:**\n36\t- `createLane()` calls `executeFn(epic.id, worktreePath)` at line 360\n37\t- `worktreePath` is the return value of `worktreeManager.createWorktree()` (line 337)\n38\t- Test `passes worktree path from WorktreeManager to executeFn` (line 181) asserts `executeFn` called with `('/tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-1')` and `('/tmp/codeharness-wt-epic-2')`\n39\t\n40\t## AC 4: Promise.race detects completion and schedules next epic\n41\t**Verdict:** PASS\n42\t**Evidence:**\n43\t- Main scheduling loop at line 215: `while (pendingEpics.length > 0 || activeLanes.size > 0)`\n44\t- `Promise.race()` at line 251 races all active lane promises\n45\t- Test `schedules next epic when a lane completes` (line 194) verifies call order `['1', '2']` with maxParallel=1\n46\t\n47\t## AC 5: Epic independence — epic N waits for lower-index epics\n48\t**Verdict:** PASS\n49\t**Evidence:**\n50\t- `isEpicReady(epicIndex)` at line 395 checks no active lane has index < epicIndex\n51\t- `findNextReadyEpic()` at line 379 iterates pending epics and uses `isEpicReady`\n52\t- Test `epic 2 does not start until epic 0 completes when maxParallel=2` (line 211) verifies C (index 2) does not start while A (index 0) is active, even though B (index 1) has completed and freed a slot\n53\t\n54\t## AC 6: LaneEvent objects are emitted\n55\t**Verdict:** PASS\n56\t**Evidence:**\n57\t- `emit()` method at line 408 iterates listeners and calls each with the event\n58\t- `onEvent()` at line 159 registers listeners\n59\t- Events emitted: `epic-queued` (line 203), `lane-started` (line 352), `lane-completed` (line 278), `lane-failed` (line 301)\n60\t- Test `emits epic-queued, lane-started, lane-completed events` (line 256) verifies all event types\n61\t\n62\t## AC 7: maxParallel=1 executes sequentially\n63\t**Verdict:** PASS\n64\t**Evidence:**\n65\t- Test `runs one epic at a time` (line 294) with maxParallel=1 and 3 epics asserts `executionOrder` is `['1', '2', '3']`\n66\t- Test `never has more than 1 concurrent execution` (line 309) tracks `maxConcurrent` and asserts it equals 1\n67\t\n68\t## AC 8: Lane failure cleans up worktree and continues\n69\t**Verdict:** PASS\n70\t**Evidence:**\n71\t- Failure handling at line 285: adds to `failedEpicIds`, records `EpicResult` with error, calls `worktreeManager.cleanupWorktree()` (line 297), emits `lane-failed` event\