{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0146uKWoiXsLB2AUQoa9iFRn","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-04 (Session 2)\n2\t\n3\t### 17-2-lane-pool — create-story (2026-04-04T20:04)\n4\t\n5\t- Sprint-status.yaml showed 17-1-worktree-manager regressed to `backlog` despite being committed as `done`. Fixed manually.\n6\t- All 12 ACs tagged `test-provable` — pure scheduling module with mocked deps.\n7\t- AC #5 epic independence ordering is simplified heuristic; post-MVP DAG approach noted.\n8\t\n9\t## Token Report\n10\t- Total tool calls: 14\n11\t- By tool: Read: 6, Glob: 6, Grep: 2, Bash: 1, Write: 1\n12\t- Largest Bash outputs: `ls implementation-artifacts` (~5 lines)\n13\t- Files read: 6 unique, 6 total reads\n14\t- Redundant operations: 3 similar glob patterns for story files\n15\t\n16\t### 17-2-lane-pool — dev-story (2026-04-04T20:16)\n17\t\n18\t- Epic independence semantics (AC #5): batch-style parallelism, not sliding-window. Epic 3 won't start until ALL preceding epics complete, even if epic 1 finishes while epic 2 is still running. Matches spec but may surprise users.\n19\t- No workarounds or TODOs.\n20\t- Empty catch blocks annotated with `// IGNORE:` per project lint rules.\n21\t\n22\t## Token Report\n23\t- Total tool calls: 20\n24\t- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 7, Edit: 4, Grep: 3, Write: 2, Glob: 2, Skill: 1\n25\t- Largest Bash outputs: `npm test` (~30 lines), first test run failure (~45 lines), `npx vitest run` (~15 lines)\n26\t- Files read: 9 unique, 9 total reads\n27\t- Redundant operations: none\n28\t\n29\t### 17-2-lane-pool — code-review (2026-04-04T20:22)\n30\t\n31\t- 0 HIGH, 3 MEDIUM (all coverage gaps — fixed), 3 LOW (unreachable defensive code)\n32\t- Coverage after fixes: 100% statements, 91.17% branches, 100% functions, 100% lines\n33\t- LOW: Unreachable `?? 'Unknown error'` fallback and `activeIndex !== undefined` guard — defensive but unnecessary\n34\t- LOW: No test for pool reuse (calling startPool twice)\n35\t- Architecture note: candidate batching bypasses independence check for initial batch — fine for small maxParallel but could over-schedule with large values\n36\t- createWorktree uses execSync, blocking event loop — inherited from WorktreeManager design\n37\t\n38\t## Token Report\n39\t- Total tool calls: 17\n40\t- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 6, Edit: 3, Grep: 1, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n41\t- Largest Bash outputs: coverage run (~50 lines), verbose test run (~40 lines), coverage run 2 (~30 lines)\n42\t- Files read: 8 unique, 9 total reads\n43\t- Redundant operations: none\n44\t\n45\t### 17-2-lane-pool — verification (2026-04-04T20:31)\n46\t\n47\t- **`codeharness verify` precondition failure**: AGENTS.md for `src/lib` did not reference `lane-pool.ts`. Fixed by adding entry to AGENTS.md.\n48\t- **BATS test warnings**: `npm test` output polluted with BW01 warnings from BATS integration tests. Pre-existing.\n49\t- **Branch coverage 91.17%**: Uncovered branches at lines 291-306, 398 (defensive fallbacks). Stmts/funcs/lines all 100%.\n50\t- **Verification gap**: AC5 (epic independence) verified by single test with 3 epics.\n51\t\n52\t## Token Report\n53\t- Total tool calls: 14\n54\t- By tool: Bash: 10, Read: 3, Write: 1\n55\t- Largest Bash outputs: `npx vitest run --coverage` (~80 lines), `npm test` (~60 lines)\n56\t- Files read: 3 unique, 3 total reads\n57\t- Redundant operations: npm test ran twice, coverage command ran twice\n58\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01HD2FQ715hjYuGnBPGGv1RV","session_id":"be1634c4-ada6-4a14-ba2b-b0cd95b49a03","uuid":"914d43f5-e5db-42b7-a187-2c59e80ea5db","timestamp":"2026-04-03T20:37:09.365Z"}
