{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0188HfbAN5fcd5aYQweRSDXu","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Session Retrospective — 2026-04-04\n2\t\n3\t**Generated:** 2026-04-04T00:15:00Z\n4\t\n5\t---\n6\t\n7\t## 1. Session Summary\n8\t\n9\t### Stories Attempted This Session\n10\t\n11\t| Story | Phase Reached | Outcome |\n12\t|-------|--------------|---------|\n13\t| 17-1-worktree-manager | done (committed) | Completed prior session, committed as `c5385bf` |\n14\t| 17-2-lane-pool | verifying | create-story, dev-story, code-review all completed; currently in verification |\n15\t\n16\t### Sprint Progress (Cumulative)\n17\t\n18\t- **Total stories:** 64\n19\t- **Done:** 48 (75%)\n20\t- **In progress (verifying):** 1 (17-2-lane-pool)\n21\t- **Backlog:** 15 (epics 17-20 remainder)\n22\t- **Failed:** 0\n23\t- **Epics completed:** 16 of 20\n24\t\n25\t### Session Velocity\n26\t\n27\tThis session processed 2 stories through the pipeline. Story 17-1 was committed from a prior session's work. Story 17-2 completed all three subagent phases (create-story, dev-story, code-review) and is awaiting verification.\n28\t\n29\t---\n30\t\n31\t## 2. Issues Analysis\n32\t\n33\t### Issues from Session Log\n34\t\n35\t**Category: State Regression (1 issue)**\n36\t- Sprint-status.yaml showed 17-1-worktree-manager regressed from `done` to `backlog` despite being committed. Required manual fix.\n37\t- **Root cause:** sprint-status.yaml is a derived view regenerated from sprint-state.json. If the generator runs before sprint-state.json is updated, it overwrites correct status.\n38\t- **Severity:** Medium. Causes confusion but doesn't block execution.\n39\t\n40\t**Category: Design Decisions (2 issues)**\n41\t- AC #5 epic independence ordering uses simplified heuristic (batch parallelism, not sliding-window). Epic 3 won't start until ALL of epics 1+2 finish, even if epic 1 finishes early. Correct per spec but limits throughput.\n42\t- `createWorktree` uses `execSync`, blocking the event loop. Inherited from WorktreeManager design — acceptable for MVP but needs async refactor for production parallel execution.\n43\t\n44\t**Category: Code Quality (2 issues)**\n45\t- Unreachable defensive code: `?? 'Unknown error'` fallback and `activeIndex !== undefined` guard flagged as LOW by code review. Left in place as harmless.\n46\t- No test for pool reuse (calling `startPool` twice). Minor gap — not a regression risk.\n47\t\n48\t**Category: Coverage (1 issue)**\n49\t- 3 MEDIUM coverage gaps found during code review — all fixed. Final coverage: 100% statements, 91.17% branches, 100% functions, 100% lines.\n50\t\n51\t---\n52\t\n53\t## 3. Cost Analysis\n54\t\n55\t### Overall Sprint Cost\n56\t\n57\t| Metric | Value |\n58\t|--------|-------|\n59\t| Total API cost | $329.10 |\n60\t| Total API calls | 2,507 |\n61\t| Average cost per story | $3.40 |\n62\t| Stories processed | 82 (includes retries) |\n63\t\n64\t### Cost by Phase\n65\t\n66\t| Phase | Cost | % | Calls |\n67\t|-------|------|---|-------|\n68\t| verify | $146.44 | 44.5% | 1,198 |\n69\t| orchestrator | $58.82 | 17.9% | 271 |\n70\t| create-story | $36.14 | 11.0% | 315 |\n71\t| dev-story | $33.68 | 10.2% | 300 |\n72\t| code-review | $30.99 | 9.4% | 260 |\n73\t| retro | $23.03 | 7.0% | 163 |\n74\t\n75\t**Key finding:** Verification consumes 44.5% of total cost — nearly half the budget. This is the single biggest optimization target.\n76\t\n77\t### Cost by Token Type\n78\t\n79\t- **Cache reads dominate:** 135M tokens at $202.82 (62% of cost). This is expected — subagents re-read large context windows.\n80\t- **Cache writes:** $72.83 (22%). Each new subagent session primes the cache.\n81\t- **Output tokens:** $53.32 (16%). Relatively efficient — agents aren't over-generating.\n82\t\n83\t### Subagent-Level Token Breakdown (This Session)\n84\t\n85\t| Subagent | Tool Calls | Heaviest Tools | Largest Bash Output |\n86\t|----------|-----------|----------------|---------------------|\n87\t| 17-2 create-story | 14 | Read: 6, Glob: 6 | `ls implementation-artifacts` (~5 lines) |\n88\t| 17-2 dev-story | 20 | Bash: 8, Read: 7 | `npm test` failures (~45 lines) |\n89\t| 17-2 code-review | 17 | Bash: 8, Read: 6 | coverage run (~50 lines) |\n90\t\n91\t**Observations:**\n92\t- create-story ran 3 redundant glob patterns searching for story files. Could be eliminated with a single broader glob.\n93\t- dev-story's largest output was a test failure dump (45 lines) — necessary for debugging, not wasteful.\n94\t- code-review ran coverage 3 times (initial + 2 re-runs after fixes). The iterative fix-rerun cycle is inherent to the review process.\n95\t- No files were read redundantly within any single subagent this session — good discipline.\n96\t\n97\t### Most Expensive Stories (All-Time)\n98\t\n99\tThe \"unknown\" bucket at $50.51 (15.3%) represents orchestrator overhead not attributed to specific stories. Stories 5-1 ($8.84) and 2-1 ($8.51) were the most expensive named stories — both are foundational modules with complex schemas.\n100\t\n101\t---\n102\t\n103\t## 4. What Went Well\n104\t\n105\t- **Zero failures.** 48 stories done, 0 failed. Every story that entered the pipeline completed successfully.\n106\t- **Clean code review cycle.** 17-2-lane-pool had 0 HIGH issues, 3 MEDIUM issues (all fixed), final coverage at 100%/91%/100%/100%.\n107\t- **All 12 ACs tagged test-provable.** The lane-pool story is a pure scheduling module with mocked deps — ideal for automated verification.\n108\t- **Efficient subagent execution.** Total of 51 tool calls across 3 subagent phases for story 17-2 — no wasted iterations, no retries needed.\n109\t- **State management improved.** The sprint-status regression was caught and fixed immediately rather than propagating downstream.\n110\t\n111\t---\n112\t\n113\t## 5. What Went Wrong\n114\t\n115\t- **Sprint-status.yaml state regression.** Story 17-1 was marked `backlog` despite being committed. This is a recurring issue with derived state files getting out of sync with sprint-state.json.\n116\t- **execSync in WorktreeManager.** The blocking call design was flagged by code review but left as-is. For epic 17 (parallel execution), this is a design smell — worktree creation will block the event loop when lanes run in parallel. This will likely surface as a real problem in 17-3 or 18-x.\n117\t- **Verification phase cost.** At 44.5% of total spend, verification is disproportionately expensive. The 1,198 calls suggest verification subagents are doing significant redundant work across stories.\n118\t- **\"unknown\" story bucket.** $50.51 (15.3%) in unattributed costs indicates orchestrator overhead that should be tagged to specific stories for better cost attribution.\n119\t\n120\t---\n121\t\n122\t## 6. Lessons Learned\n123\t\n124\t### Patterns to Repeat\n125\t1. **Test-provable AC tagging.** Marking all ACs as test-provable upfront ensures the verification phase has clear targets. Continue this practice.\n126\t2. **Immediate state regression fixes.** Catching and fixing the sprint-status regression before proceeding prevented downstream confusion.\n127\t3. **Code review driving coverage.** The 3 MEDIUM issues found by code review were all coverage gaps — the review process is working as intended.\n128\t\n129\t### Patterns to Avoid\n130\t1. **Regenerating sprint-status.yaml without checking sprint-state.json freshness.** Add a guard or timestamp check.\n131\t2. **execSync in parallel-execution modules.** Epic 17 is about parallelism — blocking calls are a design contradiction. Flag this in the architecture for async refactor.\n132\t3. **Redundant glob patterns in create-story.** Three similar globs for story files when one broader pattern suffices.\n133\t\n134\t---\n135\t\n136\t## 7. Action Items\n137\t\n138\t| # | Action | Priority | Owner |\n139\t|---|--------|----------|-------|\n140\t| 1 | Complete verification of 17-2-lane-pool | High | harness |\n141\t| 2 | Begin 17-3-run-command-parallel-integration | High | harness |\n142\t| 3 | Investigate verification phase cost — 44.5% of total budget seems excessive. Consider caching verification results or reducing redundant file reads in verify subagents. | Medium | process |\n143\t| 4 | Fix sprint-status.yaml regeneration to check sprint-state.json timestamps before overwriting | Medium | tooling |\n144\t| 5 | Plan async refactor of WorktreeManager.createWorktree (execSync -> spawn/async) before epic 18 | Medium | architecture |\n145\t| 6 | Tag orchestrator costs to specific stories to eliminate the $50.51 \"unknown\" bucket | Low | tooling |\n146\t| 7 | Reduce redundant glob patterns in create-story subagent — use single broad pattern | Low | process |\n147\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01HD2FQ715hjYuGnBPGGv1RV","session_id":"be1634c4-ada6-4a14-ba2b-b0cd95b49a03","uuid":"a7a4a744-ba4c-4396-ba1a-3c628e07f364","timestamp":"2026-04-03T20:37:10.528Z"}
